cli/commands/command.go defines Command interface (Run(ctx Context) (Result, int); Meta() Meta), Context struct (Args, Dir, Orch), Meta struct (Name, Short, Usage, Flags), and the Version package var. The Context carries the orchestrator so commands can call orch methods. Meta is the single source of truth for command metadata. See <ref spec="output.command_interface">command interface</ref> and <ref spec="output_intent.metadata_single_source">metadata single source</ref>.